@startuml state-key-rotation

skinparam backgroundColor #FAFAFA
skinparam defaultFontName "Helvetica"
skinparam defaultFontSize 12

title Key Lifecycle & Rotation State Diagram

[*] --> Active : Key created\n(InMemoryKeyProvider)

Active : kid = "key-v1"
Active : Used for signing new tokens

Active --> Retired : New key "key-v2"\npromoted to current

Retired : kid = "key-v1"
Retired : No longer signs new tokens
Retired : Still verifies old tokens via byKid()

Retired --> Revoked : notAfter reached\nor security incident

Revoked : byKid() returns null
Revoked : All tokens signed with\nthis key rejected

Revoked --> [*]

note right of Active
  "Current" key = first key
  in InMemoryKeyProvider.
  KeySet.toJwks() exports
  all active public keys.
end note

note right of Retired
  Key rotation: add new key
  as first parameter, keep old
  as second — old URLs / JWTs
  still verify.
end note

@enduml
